{"type":"text","timestamp":1775864102718,"sessionID":"ses_28640c9ecffewH8ytSyVl0usqG","part":{"id":"prt_d79bfbd75001UUUihnn2DbVZBV","messageID":"msg_d79bfac22001rmNumNK3slq5x3","sessionID":"ses_28640c9ecffewH8ytSyVl0usqG","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the proposal.md for AR-012 based on the session store specifications provided.","time":{"start":1775864102717,"end":1775864102717}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775864174678,"sessionID":"ses_28640c9ecffewH8ytSyVl0usqG","part":{"id":"prt_d79c07dc6001oVC1klVeFEz6mk","messageID":"msg_d79bfac22001rmNumNK3slq5x3","sessionID":"ses_28640c9ecffewH8ytSyVl0usqG","type":"text","text":"_DISABLE","time":{"start":1775864174675,"end":1775864174675}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864174724,"sessionID":"ses_28640c9ecffewH8ytSyVl0usqG","part":{"id":"prt_d79bfbf3f0012O0MTqCTNwKMac","messageID":"msg_d79bfac22001rmNumNK3slq5x3","sessionID":"ses_28640c9ecffewH8ytSyVl0usqG","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义 (Session Store Interface Definition)\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine and implement a unified `Store` interface in `pkg/store` to persist sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with support for Redis and Valkey backends. The Session Store provides the persistence foundation for AgentCube's session management, enabling:\n\n1. **Session Persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox metadata by session ID in JSON format\n2. **Expiry Tracking**: Maintain a sorted set index (`session:expiry`) for garbage collection of expired sessions\n3. **Activity Tracking**: Maintain a sorted set index (`session:last_activity`) for idle session detection and cleanup\n4. **Multi-Backend Support**: Pluggable implementation supporting both Redis (go-redis/v9) and Valkey (valkey-go)\n\nThis AR establishes the storage abstraction layer that enables the Router and WorkloadManager to manage session lifecycle, support session recovery, and implement idle/expiration cleanup policies.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` |\n| **Core interface** | `Store` interface with 8 methods (Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close) |\n| **Implementations** | Redis (`store_redis.go`) and Valkey (`store_valkey.go`) providers |\n| **Data types** | `types.SandboxInfo`, `types.SandboxEntryPoint` |\n| **Error handling** | `ErrNotFound` sentinel error |\n| **Singleton access** | `Storage()` function with `sync.Once` initialization |\n| **Index management** | ZSET-based expiry and last-activity indices |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- SQL database implementations (MySQL, PostgreSQL) - can be added later via same interface\n- Cluster-wide distributed locking (handled by Kubernetes controllers)\n- Encryption at rest (rely on Redis/Valkey TLS and Kubernetes network policies)\n- Multi-region replication (rely on Redis/Valkey native clustering)\n- Transactional multi-key atomic operations across different session IDs\n- Custom serialization formats (JSON only)\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | **NEW** — `Store` interface definition, `ErrNotFound`, provider type constants |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | **NEW** — `Storage()` singleton accessor, `initStore()` with `sync.Once` |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | **NEW** — Redis implementation using go-redis/v9 |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | **NEW** — Valkey implementation using valkey-go |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`Store`** — Primary interface:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n**`redisStore`** — Redis implementation struct:\n\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n    sessionPrefix        string           // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string           // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string           // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n```\n\n**`valkeyStore`** — Valkey implementation struct:\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client    // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n    sessionPrefix        string           // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string           // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string           // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n```\n\n**`types.SandboxInfo`** — Stored document type:\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n    SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Operations Flow\n\n#### StoreSandbox (Atomic Write)\n\n```\nStoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n         │\n         ▼\n    Validate: sandbox != nil && !ExpiresAt.IsZero()\n         │\n         ▼\n    Serialize to JSON\n         │\n         ▼\n    Pipeline/Multi:\n    ├─ SETNX session:{id} <json>\n    ├─ ZADD session:expiry <expiresAt.Unix> {id}\n    └─ ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix> {id}\n         │\n         ▼\n    Return error if any command fails\n```\n\n#### GetSandboxBySessionID\n\n```\nGetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n         │\n         ▼\n    GET session:{sessionID}\n         │\n         ▼\n    If key not exists:\n         └── Return ErrNotFound\n    If exists:\n         └── Unmarshal JSON → *SandboxInfo\n```\n\n#### UpdateSandbox\n\n```\nUpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n         │\n         ▼\n    Validate: sandbox != nil\n         │\n         ▼\n    Serialize to JSON\n         │\n         ▼\n    SET session:{id} <json> XX  (key must exist)\n         │\n         ▼\n    If SETXX returns false:\n         └── Return error (key not exists)\n    Note: Does NOT modify ZSET indices\n```\n\n#### DeleteSandboxBySessionID (Atomic Cleanup)\n\n```\nDeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n         │\n         ▼\n    Pipeline/Multi:\n    ├─ DEL session:{id}\n    ├─ ZREM session:expiry {id}\n    └─ ZREM session:last_activity {id}\n         │\n         ▼\n    Return error if any command fails\n```\n\n#### ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n```\nListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n         │\n         ▼\n    If limit <= 0: return nil, nil\n         │\n         ▼\n    ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 {limit}\n         │\n         ▼\n    For each sessionID returned:\n         ├─ GET session:{id}\n         ├─ If key exists: unmarshal and collect\n         └─ If key missing: skip (orphan ZSET member)\n         │\n         ▼\n    Return []*SandboxInfo\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n| Name | Value | Description |\n|------|-------|-------------|\n| `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Key prefix for session data |\n| `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET key for expiry tracking |\n| `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET key for activity tracking |\n| `redisStoreType` | `\"redis\"` | Provider type constant |\n| `valkeyStoreType` | `\"valkey\"` | Provider type constant |\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n**Redis:**\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection (case-insensitive) |\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n\n**Valkey:**\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | Yes | - | Must be `valkey` |\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated server addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | - | Set `\"true\"` to enable `DisableCache` |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | - | Set `\"true\"` to enable `ForceSingleClient` |\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files created/modified\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | ~80 | New |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | ~60 | New |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | ~200 | New |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | ~220 | New |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| Router (AR-009) | Uses `Storage()` to persist session metadata |\n| Session Manager (AR-010) | Uses store for session CRUD operations |\n| Idle Cleanup Controller | Uses `ListInactiveSandboxes` and `ListExpiredSandboxes` |\n| WorkloadManager | Uses store for sandbox metadata persistence |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None for existing APIs**: This is a new package\n- **Interface stability**: Store interface is designed to be backend-agnostic\n- **Key naming**: Uses namespaced keys (`session:` prefix) to avoid conflicts\n- **Error contract**: `ErrNotFound` sentinel provides stable error checking\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Use Kubernetes CRDs for session storage\n\n**Approach**: Store session metadata as Kubernetes custom resources (AgentRuntime objects with session labels).\n\n**Rejected because**: CRDs have higher latency and are not designed for high-frequency read/write operations. Session storage requires frequent activity timestamp updates and fast lookups by session ID, which are better suited for in-memory databases like Redis/Valkey.\n\n### 2. Use a single SQL database (PostgreSQL/MySQL)\n\n**Approach**: Implement Store interface using SQL with indexed columns for expiry and last_activity.\n\n**Rejected because**: While SQL provides ACID guarantees, it adds operational complexity (schema migrations, connection pooling). Redis/Valkey provide better performance for simple key-value operations and native sorted set support for time-based queries. SQL can be added later as another implementation.\n\n### 3. Use etcd directly\n\n**Approach**: Store sessions in Kubernetes etcd with custom prefix.\n\n**Rejected because**: etcd is optimized for configuration data, not high-frequency session metadata. It would add load to the Kubernetes control plane and require careful quota management.\n\n### 4. Use Redis Cluster vs. standalone\n\n**Approach**: Require Redis Cluster for production deployments.\n\n**Rejected because**: Both Redis standalone and Cluster modes are supported through the go-redis library. The implementation uses single-node commands (SET, GET, ZADD) which work in both modes. Cluster-specific configuration is handled via environment variables, not code changes.\n\n### 5. Use hash tags for Redis Cluster\n\n**Approach**: Use `{session}` hash tags in keys to ensure all session keys map to the same slot.\n\n**Considered**: The current implementation uses simple prefixes. Hash tags can be added if cluster deployments require it, as the key generation is centralized in `sessionKey()` helper functions.\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.x | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | - | SandboxInfo type definition |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests for store package\nmake test PKG=./pkg/store/...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/store/...\n\n# Integration tests (requires Redis/Valkey)\ngo test -v ./pkg/store/... -run \"TestRedis\" -redis-addr=localhost:6379\ngo test -v ./pkg/store/... -run \"TestValkey\" -valkey-addr=localhost:6379\n\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/store/...\n\n# Verify interface compliance\ngo build ./...\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [Session Store Design](session-store/design.md) — Detailed design document\n- [Session Store Specification](session-store/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n- [Redis Commands](https://redis.io/commands/) — Redis command reference\n- [Valkey Go Client](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go) — Valkey client documentation\n\n---\n\n*AR-012 — Module: pkg/store — Language: Go — Size: S*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775864174681,"end":1775864174721}}}}
