{"type":"text","timestamp":1775864260785,"sessionID":"ses_28640c9ecffewH8ytSyVl0usqG","part":{"id":"prt_d79c1e111001k4K9HoUCLmUxEo","messageID":"msg_d79c17748001rBewGmDLg65Mko","sessionID":"ses_28640c9ecffewH8ytSyVl0usqG","type":"text","text":"Done! I've written `proposal.md` for AR-012 — Session Store Interface Definition at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md`.\n\nThe proposal includes:\n\n| Section | Content |\n|---------|---------|\n| **Purpose** | Unified Store interface for sandbox metadata persistence with Redis/Valkey backends |\n| **Scope** | Store interface (8 methods), Redis & Valkey implementations, singleton access, ZSET indices |\n| **Design** | 4 new files (`store.go`, `singleton.go`, `store_redis.go`, `store_valkey.go`), type definitions, operation flows |\n| **Impact Analysis** | ~560 lines estimated, downstream consumers (Router, Session Manager, Idle Cleanup) |\n| **Alternatives Considered** | K8s CRDs (rejected - latency), SQL (rejected - complexity), etcd (rejected - control plane load) |\n| **Dependencies** | go-redis/v9, valkey-go, klog/v2 |\n| **Verification** | Unit tests, race detection, integration tests |\n\nKey design decisions:\n- **Dual backend support**: Redis (go-redis/v9) and Valkey (valkey-go) via `STORE_TYPE` environment variable\n- **ZSET indices**: `session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` for efficient time-range queries\n- **Singleton pattern**: `Storage()` function with `sync.Once` for thread-safe initialization\n- **Error contract**: `ErrNotFound` sentinel for missing session keys","time":{"start":1775864260781,"end":1775864260781}}}
